{
  "id": "spring-shm",
  "title": "A mass on a spring",
  "topic": "shm",
  "slug": "mass-spring",
  "scenario": "A 1 kg mass on a spring (k = 4 N/m) is pulled 0.3 m from equilibrium and released from rest. How does it move — and where does the period the algebra course made you memorize actually come from?",
  "regime": 2,
  "constants": {
    "m": 1.0,
    "k": 4.0
  },
  "initial_conditions": {
    "x0": 0.3,
    "v0": 0.0
  },
  "assumptions": [
    {
      "claim": "Ideal spring obeying Hooke's law: the restoring force is proportional to displacement.",
      "kind": "model"
    },
    {
      "claim": "No friction or air resistance (undamped motion).",
      "kind": "model"
    },
    {
      "claim": "The mass is a point and the spring is massless.",
      "kind": "model"
    }
  ],
  "algebra": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "label": "What the algebra-based course hands you (memorized, no derivation)",
        "latex": "T = 2\\pi\\sqrt{\\tfrac{m}{k}} \\qquad v_{\\max} = \\omega A",
        "prose": "You are told the motion is sinusoidal and given the period to memorize — but not *why* the motion is a cosine, or where the period comes from. Calculus is the only road to the why."
      }
    ],
    "result": {
      "angular_frequency": {
        "label": "Angular frequency $\\omega = \\sqrt{k/m}$",
        "unit": "rad/s",
        "symbolic_latex": "\\omega",
        "value": 2.0,
        "display": "2"
      },
      "period": {
        "label": "Period $T = 2\\pi/\\omega$",
        "unit": "s",
        "symbolic_latex": "\\frac{2 \\pi}{\\omega}",
        "value": 3.141593,
        "display": "3.142"
      },
      "amplitude": {
        "label": "Amplitude",
        "unit": "m",
        "symbolic_latex": "\\sqrt{x_{0}^{2} + \\frac{v_{0}^{2}}{\\omega^{2}}}",
        "value": 0.3,
        "display": "0.3"
      },
      "max_speed": {
        "label": "Maximum speed $\\omega A$",
        "unit": "m/s",
        "symbolic_latex": "\\omega \\sqrt{x_{0}^{2} + \\frac{v_{0}^{2}}{\\omega^{2}}}",
        "value": 0.6,
        "display": "0.6"
      }
    }
  },
  "calculus": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "label": "Newton's second law with Hooke's law",
        "latex": "m\\,x'' = -k\\,x \\;\\;\\Longrightarrow\\;\\; x'' = -\\omega^2 x,\\quad \\omega^2 = \\tfrac{k}{m}",
        "prose": "The spring force is proportional to displacement and points back toward equilibrium. This is the equation of motion — a differential equation, not an algebra formula."
      },
      {
        "label": "Solve the equation of motion",
        "latex": "x(t) = x_0\\cos\\omega t + \\tfrac{v_0}{\\omega}\\sin\\omega t",
        "prose": "The function whose second derivative is −ω² times itself is a sinusoid. The two constants are fixed by the initial position and velocity."
      },
      {
        "label": "Differentiate for velocity and acceleration",
        "latex": "v(t) = -x_0\\,\\omega\\sin\\omega t + v_0\\cos\\omega t,\\qquad a(t) = -\\omega^2 x(t)",
        "prose": "Acceleration is always −ω² times the displacement: largest at the extremes, zero at equilibrium. On the stacked graph, v leads x by a quarter period."
      },
      {
        "label": "The memorized period emerges",
        "latex": "\\boxed{\\,T = \\dfrac{2\\pi}{\\omega} = 2\\pi\\sqrt{\\dfrac{m}{k}}\\,}",
        "prose": "The cosine repeats every 2π/ω — and SymPy proves x(t+T) = x(t). The result the algebra course made you memorize is exactly the period of the solution.",
        "emphasis": true
      }
    ]
  },
  "proof": {
    "kind": "governing",
    "heading": "The closed form provably solves the equation of motion — and the memorized period falls out.",
    "checked_by": "sympy",
    "holds": true,
    "detail": "back-substitute $x(t)$ into $x'' = -\\omega^2 x$; check the initial conditions; check $\\tfrac{d}{dt}\\,\\mathrm{energy} = 0$; check periodicity",
    "checks": [
      {
        "key": "solves_eom",
        "claim": "The closed form solves the equation of motion $x'' = -\\omega^2 x$.",
        "holds": true,
        "tier": "structural"
      },
      {
        "key": "ic_position",
        "claim": "It matches the initial position $x(0) = x_0$.",
        "holds": true,
        "tier": "structural"
      },
      {
        "key": "ic_velocity",
        "claim": "It matches the initial velocity $x'(0) = v_0$.",
        "holds": true,
        "tier": "structural"
      },
      {
        "key": "energy_conserved",
        "claim": "Total energy $\\tfrac12 v^2 + \\tfrac12 \\omega^2 x^2$ is conserved (its time-derivative is zero).",
        "holds": true,
        "tier": "structural"
      },
      {
        "key": "period_falls_out",
        "claim": "The memorized period $T = 2\\pi/\\omega$ falls out: $x(t+T) = x(t)$.",
        "holds": true,
        "tier": "structural"
      }
    ]
  },
