  "misconception": {
    "claim": "The mass moves fastest at the ends of its swing (the turning points).",
    "refuted_by": "At a turning point the speed is zero — that is where it reverses. It moves fastest through equilibrium ($x = 0$), where the v-t graph peaks a quarter-period out of phase with x-t. Acceleration, $a = -\\omega^2 x$, is largest at the ends and zero in the middle."
  },
